The error occurs because you're trying to override a dynamically created method (`foo`) in the child class. In R6, when you define a method in a class definition, R6 creates a locked binding for it. When the parent's `initialize()` runs, it tries to create the same method dynamically, causing a conflict with the locked binding.

## Solution

Define the method in the parent class definition instead of creating it dynamically:

```r
